 2009-02312009-02-12,  ,  ,  HERITAGE, 
ActCanadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission Act
PrecisReappointment of ELIZABETH A. DUNCAN of Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, to be a full-time member of the Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission to hold office during good behaviour for a term of five years; designate ELIZABETH A. DUNCAN for the Atlantic region, as established under subsection 10(1.1) of that Act; and determine that ELIZABETH A. DUNCAN shall reside within 100 kilometres of the Atlantic regional office; effective May 2, 2009.
